  {
    "fixture_id": "wire-8",
    "description": "Batching: with batchSize > 1, a single tracked event is buffered, not sent — zero HTTP calls before flush",
    "constructor": { "apiKey": "test-key", "env": "staging", "version": "1.0.0", "appName": "TestApp", "batchSize": 30 },
    "operation": "trackSchemaFromEvent",
    "input": {
      "eventName": "Buffered Event",
      "eventProperties": { "plan": "pro" },
      "streamId": "stream-batch"
    },
    "mock_response": null,
    "expected_request_count": 0,
    "expected_promise_outcome": "resolve",
    "notes": "Batching is active because env is 'staging' (so batchSize is NOT forced to 1) and batchSize is 30. A single trackSchemaFromEvent enqueues one event, which is below the size threshold, so the SDK MUST NOT send an HTTP request before a flush — the suite runner verifies zero captured requests. The promise still resolves (with the extracted schema) at enqueue time (SPEC.md §4.2, §7.5.2). The harness invocation completes well within batchFlushSeconds (30s), so no time-based flush occurs. This is the only batching behavior the single-invocation harness can assert automatically; flush()-drains, size-triggered flush, max-queue overflow, and no-requeue-on-rejection are now covered by the dedicated batching suite (batch-1 through batch-6). Only time-based flush and transient-failure drop remain in the manual matrix in conformance/README.md (they need a controllable clock and a connection-drop mock)."
  }
]
